pageContext.description: Dimensions: EL 139.3mm; Wbl 38.8mm; Ts (at break) 1.5-3.0; EDs 75.3 (?+),Typology: evenly rounded midrib, fairly well defined angles with wings; very slight traces of edge bevel on some wings; s. hollow protrudes little into inside wings.,Condition: edges little irregular and sharp - patina flaked; odd larger notches - anc. damage; most of main fracture probably recent; dents along midrib and bend along length - anc. damage;
pageContext.surface: Dark brown-green patina; flaked at edges and on part of midrib to grey-green dry surface.
pageContext.collection: London, Society of Antiquaries Collection, B49 (iii)
pageContext.site: Unprovenanced,Alt Site: Shropshire, Little Wenlock, Willowmoor, c. SJ 6403 0830,No recorded provenance, quite possibly from Willowmoor hoard (See AFI)
